      <akn:section eId="sec_38_2572_02">
        <akn:num>38-2572.02</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Hearing officer selection.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-2572_02_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>OSSE shall administer impartial due process hearings as required by IDEA (20 U.S.C. ยง 1415(f) and 20 U.S.C. ยง 1439(a)(1)) and may issue regulations necessary for this purpose.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-2572_02_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>In selecting hearing officers for administering special education due process hearings, OSSE shall submit potential candidates for review to a 7-member community review panel.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-2572_02_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p></akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_38-2572_02_d">
      <akn:num>(d)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Following its review of candidates for hearing officers, the community review panel shall forward its recommendations to the State Superintendent of Education.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
